Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.06,0:00:06.23,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,Alchemy is a science where one understands the structure of matter, breaks it down, then rebuilds it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.23,0:00:11.86,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,However, it is not an all-powerful technique,\Nas one cannot create something out of nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.57,0:00:17.66,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,If one wishes to gain something,\None must present something of equal value.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.66,0:00:22.37,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,This is the concept of equivalent exchange, the fundamental basis of alchemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.00,0:00:27.00,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,However, there is a taboo in alchemy. Human transmutation.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.00,0:00:29.34,Default,Narr,0000,0000,0000,,One must not commit this act.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.80,0:02:03.39,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,To obtain more information about\Nthe transmutation of living organisms,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.39,0:02:08.31,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Ed and Al visited Shou Tucker, the Sewing-Life Alchemist.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.31,0:02:12.90,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,At his house, they met his daughter, Nina, and their dog, Alexander.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.32,0:02:21.62,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,In order to pass the assessment for State Alchemists,\NTucker transmuted a chimera using Nina and Alexander.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.62,0:02:24.79,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Nina will never be able to return to her old self.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.41,0:02:29.50,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Ed was grief-stricken by his powerlessness.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.59,0:02:39.09,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Mom! Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.09,0:02:40.63,Default,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter, Ed?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.68,0:02:42.85,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,A present for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.22,0:02:44.93,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I transmuted it myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.93,0:02:46.10,Default,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.56,0:02:48.35,Default,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,You're Daddy's son, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.93,0:02:50.10,Default,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.10,0:02:51.98,Default,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,You're really amazing, Ed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.98,0:02:54.44,Default,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,To be able to make something wonderful like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.19,0:02:55.94,Default,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.03,0:03:02.32,Default,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,You... couldn't make me correctly, could you...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.95,0:03:05.08,Default,Nina,0000,0000,0000,,Onii-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.41,0:03:08.50,Default,Nina,0000,0000,0000,,Let's play.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.83,0:03:16.21,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right, Brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.00,0:03:18.26,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Seemed like you were having a nightmare.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.19,0:03:38.28,Default,Riza,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter, you two? Isn't it\Na bit early in the morning to be here?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.65,0:03:40.78,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.19,0:03:43.32,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,So what's going to happen to Tucker and Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.62,0:03:50.20,Default,Riza,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Tucker was supposed to be put on trial\Nand have his State Alchemist qualifications stripped...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.21,0:03:53.04,Default,Riza,0000,0000,0000,,...but both of them died.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.04,0:03:53.71,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,"Died"?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.67,0:03:58.50,Default,Riza,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go ahead and let you know now, since you'll find out sooner or later.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.50,0:03:59.84,Default,Riza,0000,0000,0000,,They were killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.46,0:04:01.59,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.05,0:04:02.88,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,By who?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.88,0:04:03.97,Default,Riza,0000,0000,0000,,We don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.97,0:04:06.09,Default,Riza,0000,0000,0000,,I'm about to head to the scene myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.26,0:04:07.85,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,We're coming with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.85,0:04:08.35,Default,Riza,0000,0000,0000,,I can't allow you to.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.51,0:04:09.56,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Why not?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.98,0:04:13.27,Default,Riza,0000,0000,0000,,You're better off not seeing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.98,0:04:19.07,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like we were a bit late.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.07,0:04:22.03,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,We'll have to go after him soon. Or else...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.20,0:04:26.82,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,You sound as if you knew this was going to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.82,0:04:27.82,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,What's this about?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.33,0:04:35.08,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,God has given us a trial!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.08,0:04:42.63,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Evil heathens are trying to disturb our faith by spreading absurd rumors, and the military is planning to oppress us!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.01,0:04:44.88,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,But we shall not give in!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.55,0:04:48.26,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Take up arms and rise!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.26,0:04:50.89,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,In the name of our almighty Sun God, Leto!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.89,0:04:54.48,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,That's right! We've got the Sun God Leto on our side!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.48,0:04:56.23,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,Shoot the heathens!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.44,0:04:58.15,Default,Guy3,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Don't let him trick you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.15,0:05:00.98,Default,Guy3,0000,0000,0000,,That bastard has been lying to us!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.98,0:05:02.07,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.07,0:05:04.74,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,You guys are agents of the heathens, aren't you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.65,0:05:08.74,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,Humans are oh so silly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.17,0:05:21.34,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you agree, Gluttony?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.34,0:05:23.30,Default,Glut,0000,0000,0000,,Foolish! Foolish!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.30,0:05:24.88,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.67,0:05:27.72,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,Oh my, Sir High Priest.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.72,0:05:29.22,Default,Glut,0000,0000,0000,,Sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.22,0:05:31.60,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for giving you so much trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.26,0:05:36.60,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be returning to my assigned town once all of this is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.81,0:05:42.61,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,The fullmetal boy got in our way, but we were able to make good use of him in the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.94,0:05:45.11,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like this'll be over quicker than we'd expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.65,0:05:52.03,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,All of this happened just because you manipulated a bit of information and I stirred the believers.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.03,0:05:55.12,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,Humans are such simple beings.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.87,0:05:59.83,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,Blood calls for blood, while hatred begets hatred,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.83,0:06:04.59,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,and the energy that comes forth begins to take root in this earth and engraves a crest of blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.76,0:06:08.97,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,They never learn, no matter how many times history is repeated.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.38,0:06:12.35,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,Humans are foolish, sorrowful creatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.76,0:06:15.52,Default,Cor,0000,0000,0000,,But that's why we can have them play right into our hands, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.18,0:06:19.52,Default,Glut,0000,0000,0000,,Will more people die?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.52,0:06:21.15,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, they will.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.15,0:06:23.52,Default,Glut,0000,0000,0000,,Can I eat all the ones that died?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.52,0:06:24.90,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,No eating.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.19,0:06:28.61,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,In any case Envy, just how much longer do you plan to stay in that form?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.61,0:06:30.16,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,It's kind of gross.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.16,0:06:32.49,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,Oh come on, I'm just going with the flow.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.53,0:06:39.08,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,But I guess it's better to transform into someone young and cute, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.63,0:06:44.09,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,M-Monster!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.42,0:06:45.59,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.59,0:06:46.38,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,The High Priest...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.38,0:06:49.30,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to the real High Priest?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.30,0:06:50.47,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,What do we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.47,0:06:53.89,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,He called me a monster. How rude.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.89,0:06:55.43,Default,Glut,0000,0000,0000,,Can I eat him?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.06,0:07:03.77,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,Oh yeah, I heard Shou Tucker from East City was killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.77,0:07:05.36,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,Tucker?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.36,0:07:07.94,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,Ah well, who cares about small fry like him?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.94,0:07:10.86,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,Well, the guy who killed him is none other than that guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.70,0:07:15.58,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,If we're talking about East City, isn't the Flame Colonel stationed there?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.58,0:07:19.08,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,Yup. The fullmetal brat is there, too, it seems.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.08,0:07:20.37,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,Fullmetal...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.91,0:07:26.04,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,It makes me mad that he interfered with our work, but we can't let him die.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.46,0:07:28.55,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,He's an important human sacrifice, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.30,0:07:30.80,Default,Glut,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for the meal!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.22,0:07:33.80,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,Got it. We'll take care of it somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.14,0:07:37.68,Default,Lust,0000,0000,0000,,So, what's that guy's name again?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.60,0:07:39.68,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Scar?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.06,0:07:41.39,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Scarred man...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.39,0:07:45.23,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. We don't know anything about him,\Nso that's what we call him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.23,0:07:47.90,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,We have no idea what his aim is, and he's extremely elusive.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.57,0:07:52.78,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,All we know about him is that\Nhe has a large scar on his forehead.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.36,0:07:55.41,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard rumors about him, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.41,0:07:57.28,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,So that's who you guys have been after.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.83,0:08:00.37,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,It was on the recommendations from military police headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.37,0:08:03.00,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,I've got so much work from the chamber of military, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.00,0:08:04.33,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously, all this is giving me a headache...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.33,0:08:10.80,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,We've got five casualties so far in Central, ten nationwide. All State Alchemists.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.21,0:08:14.01,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Old man Gran was killed five days ago, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.68,0:08:16.47,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Brigadier General Gran?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.47,0:08:19.56,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,He was the lead of weapons transmutation and troop combat divisions!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.56,0:08:21.93,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,That's how much trouble this guy really is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.56,0:08:26.94,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Listen to me. Deploy more guards and stay put for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.94,0:08:29.15,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,I'm asking this as a friend, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.52,0:08:33.28,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,The only famous alchemists around here were you and Tucker, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.03,0:08:34.95,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.95,0:08:42.20,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I've always been thinking.\NWhat is this alchemy we believe in?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.12,0:08:50.75,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,"Alchemy is understanding the various rules and flow that exist within matter, breaking it down, then rebuilding it."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.46,0:08:55.47,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,"This world also flows while abiding by those rules and is in a cycle."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.47,0:08:59.68,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,"Death is also a part of that flow. Accept the flow entirely."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.18,0:09:03.27,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,That's what our master always said, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.06,0:09:06.73,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.48,0:09:09.40,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,But I didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.11,0:09:11.40,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,That's why we transmuted Mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.28,0:09:17.16,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,And even now, I'm thinking whether I could somehow fix something that's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.03,0:09:21.41,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I'm an idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.95,0:09:24.37,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't grown one bit since that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.71,0:09:30.13,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I thought that rain would wash away these pent-up feelings...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.42,0:09:34.80,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,But every drop that hits my face makes me more miserable.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.09,0:09:41.55,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I can't even feel the rain hitting my skin because I have no body.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.47,0:09:44.77,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,That by itself is lonely and cruel.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.39,0:09:50.11,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I still want to return to my old body. I want to become human again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.73,0:09:55.40,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it's impossible and is against the ways of this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.61,0:10:01.03,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,You're Edward Elric, the "Fullmetal Alchemist", aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.25,0:10:06.04,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.75,0:10:16.42,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell is this about?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.01,0:10:25.35,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Who the hell is this guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.35,0:10:27.23,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad... This is bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.44,0:10:29.52,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I've got to get away!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.52,0:10:31.35,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad... This is bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.69,0:10:32.94,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Al, run!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.91,0:10:42.87,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let you get away!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.54,0:10:49.46,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.59,0:11:00.72,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Al, hang on!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.77,0:11:12.85,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit, what the hell?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.85,0:11:14.86,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't done anything to set anyone against me-
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.94,0:11:17.36,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Scratch that, I've done a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.28,0:11:20.45,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't given anyone reason to go after my life, though!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.16,0:11:29.62,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Oww...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.16,0:11:34.38,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Who the hell are you? Why are you after us?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.83,0:11:37.25,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,Think of it this way:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.25,0:11:39.63,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,If there is someone who created you,\Nthen there is someone who will destroy you, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.13,0:11:42.13,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like there's no getting out of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.64,0:11:50.14,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,You've got some guts.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.93,0:11:51.56,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.82,0:11:57.82,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,Too slow.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.78,0:12:03.57,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Al!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.54,0:12:15.08,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,It's empty?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.08,0:12:16.67,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You bastard!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.30,0:12:20.21,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,Too slow!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.72,0:12:24.68,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.93,0:12:26.30,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,Automail...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.97,0:12:30.35,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,Makes sense. I wouldn't be able to\Ndestroy it with human destruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.64,0:12:32.18,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,You guys are something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.10,0:12:36.98,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,No, Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.98,0:12:38.11,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,You should run!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.11,0:12:41.32,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot! How can I leave you behind and run?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.32,0:12:44.99,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,So you transmute by placing your hands together and forming a circle.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.45,0:12:46.36,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.95,0:12:52.12,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be destroying this annoying arm of yours, first.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.00,0:12:54.79,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Brother!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.76,0:13:06.13,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,Now you can't use alchemy anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.60,0:13:12.47,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give you a bit of time to pray to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.47,0:13:15.69,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Brother, run! Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.77,0:13:20.61,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, there isn't a god I want to pray to.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.07,0:13:24.36,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Am I the only one you're after?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.03,0:13:27.61,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Are you going to kill my brother... Al... too?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.20,0:13:30.58,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,I will, if he decides to interfere.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.58,0:13:35.87,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,But the only one to receive judgment\Nat my hands is the Fullmetal Alchemist... You...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.37,0:13:37.33,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,All right...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.71,0:13:40.54,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Then promise me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.04,0:13:43.05,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,That you won't lay a finger on my little brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.26,0:13:45.34,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.34,0:13:46.97,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,I'll keep my word.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.38,0:13:49.47,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,What are you saying... Brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.22,0:13:52.51,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing? Get out of there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.51,0:13:53.72,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Get up and run!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.60,0:13:57.10,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it... Stop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.10,0:14:00.36,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it! You bastard!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.61,0:14:03.94,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,That's far enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.94,0:14:06.49,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,You've made quite a mess of things, Scar.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.70,0:14:13.79,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be taking you into custody under the offense of murdering a series of State Alchemists.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.79,0:14:18.83,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,Alchemists are beings who alter the original form of matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.21,0:14:23.29,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, an affront to God, the creator of all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.29,0:14:26.71,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,I bring judgment, acting as God's hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.42,0:14:29.93,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,If you choose to get in my way, I will eliminate you, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.01,0:14:31.93,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.72,0:14:35.10,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want any of you interfering in this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.10,0:14:36.31,Default,Riza,0000,0000,0000,,Colonel Mustang!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.52,0:14:39.56,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,Mustang... The Flame Alchemist.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.52,0:14:43.27,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,You came to me to receive judgment,\Nsaving me the effort of having to search for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.61,0:14:45.28,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,What a splendid day!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.61,0:14:48.03,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,You know my name, yet you're picking a fight with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.19,0:14:49.24,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,What a fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.75,0:14:59.83,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,What was that for?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.83,0:15:01.58,Default,Riza,0000,0000,0000,,Colonel, please stay back.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.58,0:15:03.04,Default,Riza,0000,0000,0000,,You're impotent on rainy days, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.00,0:15:07.80,Default,Havoc,0000,0000,0000,,Oh right, I guess you can't make sparks when it's wet like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.80,0:15:11.55,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,It's awfully convenient for me if you can't make flames, State Alchemist.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.22,0:15:15.68,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,I will destroy all here who interfere with my duty!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.10,0:15:17.89,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,We'll just see about that!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.56,0:15:20.69,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,Reinforcements?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.89,0:15:25.32,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,You're quite good to be able to dodge my fist.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.19,0:15:28.44,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,You said you'd destroy everyone here, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.65,0:15:32.20,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Then try defeating me, first!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.91,0:15:36.95,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,The Strong Arm Alchemist, Alex Louis Armstrong!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.16,0:15:39.04,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,One after another...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.58,0:15:41.46,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,This must be divine guidance, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.46,0:15:42.83,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,So you won't retreat, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.25,0:15:46.21,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,To show deference to that courage, I'll show you...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.21,0:15:51.72,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,...a skill that has been passed down the Armstrong household for generations... Artistic Alchemy!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.56,0:15:59.56,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Who is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.18,0:16:02.48,Default,Havoc,0000,0000,0000,,He's the one who murdered Mr. Tucker.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.98,0:16:07.07,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It was {\i1}him{\i0\fscx30} {\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.61,0:16:10.69,Default,Havoc,0000,0000,0000,,Major! Please try not to destroy too much of the city!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.69,0:16:11.82,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,What are you saying?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.82,0:16:14.45,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Destruction and creation are like two sides of the same coin!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.45,0:16:18.58,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,You destroy and create! This, in other words,\Nis the law of the universe!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.87,0:16:20.16,Default,Riza,0000,0000,0000,,But why naked...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.16,0:16:22.08,Default,Havoc,0000,0000,0000,,That logic is crazy...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.83,0:16:26.88,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,But other Alchemists won't find it crazy, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.88,0:16:29.09,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Scar?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.92,0:16:32.84,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,So he's an Alchemist, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.84,0:16:39.35,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I see. The three transmutation processes in Alchemy are understanding, decomposition, and reconstruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.35,0:16:42.02,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,But he stops at the point of decomposition.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.98,0:16:45.35,Default,Havoc,0000,0000,0000,,He's an alchemist, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.35,0:16:48.69,Default,Havoc,0000,0000,0000,,Then he is going against "God's path", isn't he?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.65,0:16:54.90,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,But... why is he only after those who possess a state qualification?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.25,0:17:05.83,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,Agility that wouldn't be expected from\Nhis build and inhuman destructive power.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.12,0:17:07.88,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,And on top of that, alchemy...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.21,0:17:10.04,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,He's certainly troublesome, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.92,0:17:14.01,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Now you're stuck!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.01,0:17:16.43,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,...this is when he takes a big swing!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.63,0:17:17.80,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,Right here!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.47,0:17:20.39,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,He pulled back?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.02,0:17:26.89,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Did you get him?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.89,0:17:28.10,Default,Riza,0000,0000,0000,,He's fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.10,0:17:29.52,Default,Riza,0000,0000,0000,,Just one hit, a graze.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.78,0:17:35.03,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Brown skin and red eyes?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.40,0:17:38.03,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,An Ishbalan?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.16,0:17:42.54,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like I'm surrounded...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.79,0:17:45.50,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Hey now, don't move-
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.30,0:17:56.13,Default,Havoc,0000,0000,0000,,Damn, the bastard escaped into the sewers...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.13,0:17:56.84,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Don't go after him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.84,0:17:59.01,Default,Havoc,0000,0000,0000,,Like I'd go after a dangerous guy like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.76,0:18:00.85,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.22,0:18:04.22,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,You bought enough time for us to surround him, and yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.22,0:18:09.52,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,No, I was more concerned with\Nstaying alive rather than buying time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.52,0:18:11.02,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, is it over?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.52,0:18:14.03,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Lt. Colonel Hughes, where have you been?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.03,0:18:15.61,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,I was taking cover.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.61,0:18:17.95,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Why didn't you at least give support or something?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.95,0:18:24.04,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up! Don't drag an ordinary guy like me\Ninto you nonsensical mutants' all-around freak shows!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.04,0:18:26.04,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,What are you gazing off into space for?! Don't you guys have work to do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.29,0:18:28.58,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Emergency deployments within the city! And be sure to whip up a description about the suspect, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.58,0:18:29.25,Default,Men,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.08,0:18:30.88,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Alphonse...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.96,0:18:32.96,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Alphonse!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.13,0:18:37.38,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Al! Are you all right?! Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.88,0:18:41.01,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,So that's Elric's younger brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.01,0:18:43.64,Default,Arm,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like they've got their own issues...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.64,0:18:45.52,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Al! Alphonse!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.64,0:18:50.52,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you run away when\NI told you to, you stupid brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.52,0:18:53.27,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, I couldn't leave you behind and run away!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.27,0:18:55.27,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,That's exactly why I'm calling you stupid!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.53,0:19:01.28,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,What?! If I ran away, you might have been killed!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.28,0:19:03.53,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I might have not been killed, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.53,0:19:06.49,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Only an idiot would choose the path that leads to death!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.16,0:19:09.75,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Quit calling your brother an idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.75,0:19:11.04,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I'll say it as many times as I want!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.96,0:19:14.88,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,If you'd lived, continued to live, and survived,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.88,0:19:17.13,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,and continued to study alchemy,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.13,0:19:22.93,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,you could have found a way to get your limbs back\Nand maybe discovered how to save people like Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.93,0:19:27.89,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't be able to forgive you if you chose to die by throwing all of those possibilities away!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.69,0:19:34.31,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,My arm came off! You stupid brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.53,0:19:40.95,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We're really torn up, aren't we...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.11,0:19:43.57,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,How uncool.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.78,0:19:47.54,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,But... we're alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.54,0:19:49.29,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. We sure are.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.75,0:19:54.33,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,This seriously is a special all-around freak show, isn't it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.33,0:19:55.50,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for keeping it from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.04,0:19:58.50,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,No problem, I won't tell the higher-ups.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.76,0:20:01.76,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be somewhat troublesome if they find out, won't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.47,0:20:03.63,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.63,0:20:07.72,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,We can play off the part about Edward's limbs,\Nbut we can't really make up an excuse for the younger one.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.73,0:20:14.40,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,But seriously... we've got quite the ugly customer coming after us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.11,0:20:17.90,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,An Ishbalan, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.57,0:20:32.16,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Ishbalans were a tribe of people in the East\Nwho worshipped Ishvala as their sole creator and God.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.96,0:20:37.17,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,There were a few cases of feuds after we annexed the country,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.79,0:20:39.34,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,But thirteen years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.34,0:20:45.64,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,...when a military officer mistakenly shot and killed\Nan Ishbalan child, the situation devolved into a civil war.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.43,0:20:55.52,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,A riot called forth more riots, and the civil war eventually spread throughout all of the east.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.10,0:21:01.11,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,The order given from the highest level of\Nour military after seven years of battle was...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.32,0:21:04.24,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,...Ishbalan extermination.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.15,0:21:08.91,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Many State Alchemists were roped in to act as human weapons.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.17,0:21:21.05,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,And the State Alchemists brought forth remarkable achievements.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.67,0:21:27.18,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,That's why that man, who is a survivor of the Ishbalans, has a legitimate reason for wanting revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.18,0:21:29.10,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Bullshit!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.10,0:21:33.72,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,There's no legitimacy in revenge that drags in people who have nothing to do with it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.72,0:21:39.06,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx99}All he's doing is sugar-coating an ugly spirit of vengeance by calling himself God's hand and pretending to be all noble!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.81,0:21:42.61,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,But the hard truth is he's hostile toward us.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.36,0:21:45.57,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,And we can't die, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.36,0:21:48.45,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,The next time we see him, we'll crush him...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.74,0:21:49.78,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,...without any questions asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.78,0:21:50.70,Default,Every,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.87,0:21:57.71,Default,Hughes,0000,0000,0000,,Ed, Al, what do you two plan on doing now?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.25,0:22:01.04,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to move forward again.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.04,0:22:04.21,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We can't come to a stop as long as we're alive, after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.55,0:22:05.59,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.26,0:22:10.89,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,First off, I need to get my arm fixed in order to get your body back to normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.89,0:22:14.89,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Since I'm the only one who knows how to affix a soul to an armor.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.89,0:22:15.77,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,You're right about that!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.77,0:22:18.27,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Guess we've got no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.73,0:22:20.52,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,What do you say we go and visit our mechanic?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.52,0:22:23.02,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We haven't shown our faces there in a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.25,0:24:07.42,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Winry's smile greets Ed and Al, who return\Nto Resembool to rest their battle-wounded bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.42,0:24:14.01,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,On the other hand, a philosopher's stone\Nappears before them, shrouded in a deep mystery.{Multiple stones exist now, so no capitalization anymore}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.51,0:24:18.47,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, Fullmetal Alchemist:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.81,0:24:21.06,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 6, The Road of Hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.68,0:24:26.61,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,The wind blows through the hill in the sunset.\NWhat does it bring the boy?
